Spec compliance review found critical issues with the test code. Production code is correct. Fix the following:

## Issues to Fix

1. **Wrong filename**: Rename `SsnEncryptionHelperIntegrationTest.java` → `SsnEncryptionHelperTest.java`
2. **Wrong test type**: Must be a **unit test**, NOT an integration test. Remove `extends IntegrationTest` and `@Autowired`.
3. **Must use Mockito mocks**: `EncryptionFieldHelper` must be a Mockito mock, not a real Spring bean.
4. **Must verify mock interactions**: `verifyZeroInteractions(mockHelper)` when flag is OFF, `verify(mockHelper).encrypt(...)` when flag is ON.

## What To Do

1. Delete `src/test/java/com/hm/crypto/SsnEncryptionHelperIntegrationTest.java`
2. Create `src/test/java/com/hm/crypto/SsnEncryptionHelperTest.java` with this exact content:

```java
package com.hm.crypto;

import com.hm.feature.FeatureFlagReader;
import com.ktown4u.masking.crypto.EncryptionFieldHelper;
import org.junit.Before;
import org.junit.Test;

import static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;
import static org.mockito.Mockito.mock;
import static org.mockito.Mockito.verify;
import static org.mockito.Mockito.verifyZeroInteractions;
import static org.mockito.Mockito.when;

public class SsnEncryptionHelperTest {
    private SsnEncryptionHelper sut;
    private EncryptionFieldHelper mockHelper;

    @Before
    public void setUp() {
        sut = new SsnEncryptionHelper();
        mockHelper = mock(EncryptionFieldHelper.class);
        sut.setHelper(mockHelper);
    }

    @Test
    public void encrypt_whenFlagOff_returnsNull() {
        sut.setFeatureFlagReader(flagReader(false));

        String result = sut.encrypt("1234567890");

        assertThat(result).isNull();
        verifyZeroInteractions(mockHelper);
    }

    @Test
    public void encrypt_whenFlagOn_returnsEncryptedValue() {
        sut.setFeatureFlagReader(flagReader(true));
        when(mockHelper.encrypt("1234567890")).thenReturn("AQICAHh...encrypted");

        String result = sut.encrypt("1234567890");

        assertThat(result).isEqualTo("AQICAHh...encrypted");
        verify(mockHelper).encrypt("1234567890");
    }

    @Test
    public void encrypt_whenFlagOn_andInputNull_returnsNull() {
        sut.setFeatureFlagReader(flagReader(true));

        assertThat(sut.encrypt(null)).isNull();
        verifyZeroInteractions(mockHelper);
    }

    @Test
    public void encrypt_whenFlagOn_andInputEmpty_returnsNull() {
        sut.setFeatureFlagReader(flagReader(true));

        assertThat(sut.encrypt("")).isNull();
        verifyZeroInteractions(mockHelper);
    }

    private FeatureFlagReader flagReader(final boolean active) {
        return new FeatureFlagReader() {
            @Override
            public boolean isActive(final String feature) {
                return active;
            }
        };
    }
}
```

